Determine overall classroom dimensions: ~15 meters wide x 10 meters long x 3 meters high to comfortably fit 20 student desks in 4 rows of 5 with aisles, a teacher area, and additional furniture.\n2. Create the classroom floor: a flat plane matching the above dimensions.\n3. Build four walls (front, back, left, right) around the floor, with a height of 3 meters.\n4. Add a simple flat ceiling at 3 meters high.\n5. Define 20 student desk objects: each a rectangular table (approx. 1.2m x 0.6m x 0.75m) and one chair (0.5m x 0.5m x 0.9m). Assign light wood material.\n6. Arrange the 20 student desks and chairs in 4 rows by 5 columns, with uniform spacing (≥1.5m row spacing, ≥1m column spacing) and aisles for walking. Ensure chairs face the front.\n7. Define a teacher desk (2m x 0.8m x 0.75m) and matching chair (0.6m x 0.6m x 1m) in darker wood. Place at front-center of room, facing student desks.\n8. Create a large rectangular whiteboard (3m x 1.5m) and mount it on the front wall directly behind the teacher desk at eye level (~1m above floor).\n9. Add a ceiling-mounted projector: aligned on the centerline of the room at ~2.7m height, aimed at the whiteboard.\n10. Define and place a tall bookshelf (2m h x 1m w x 0.4m d) filled with book objects against the right side wall.\n11. Define and mount a circular wall clock (0.5m diameter) on the left side wall near the ceiling.\n12. Create a potted plant object (0.5m diameter pot, ~1m tall) and place it in the front-left corner near the entrance.\n13. Lay out multiple ceiling lights (e.g., 12 fixtures) in a 3x4 grid evenly spaced across the ceiling.\n14. Create wall poster objects (e.g., 4 educational charts, 1m x 0.7m each) and mount them on side and back walls.\n15. Define two waste bin objects (0.4m x 0.4m x 0.6m) and position one near the teacher’s desk and one at the back of the classroom.\n16. Add two large windows (2m w x 1.5m h) with curtains on the left wall, spaced evenly, at ~1.2m above floor.\n17. Apply materials: walls and floor in white or light neutral color; desks and chairs in specified wood tones; curtains in complementary light fabric.\n18. Verify all objects are placed at proper heights: desks and chairs on floor, mounted items on walls/ceiling.\n19. Check for ample walking space, no collisions, and correct orientation of all seating.\n\n            Use these relations for the objects: [\'classroom_bounds | middle\', \'floor | middle | height: Determine overall classroom dimensions: ~15 meters wide x 10 meters long x 3 meters high to comfortably fit 20 student desks in 4 rows of 5 with aisles, a teacher area, and additional furniture.\n2. Create the classroom floor: a flat plane matching the above dimensions.\n3. Build four walls (front, back, left, right) around the floor, with a height of 3 meters.\n4. Add a simple flat ceiling at 3 meters high.\n5. Define 20 student desk objects: each a rectangular table (approx. 1.2m x 0.6m x 0.75m) and one chair (0.5m x 0.5m x 0.9m). Assign light wood material.\n6. Arrange the 20 student desks and chairs in 4 rows by 5 columns, with uniform spacing (≥1.5m row spacing, ≥1m column spacing) and aisles for walking. Ensure chairs face the front.\n7. Define a teacher desk (2m x 0.8m x 0.75m) and matching chair (0.6m x 0.6m x 1m) in darker wood. Place at front-center of room, facing student desks.\n8. Create a large rectangular whiteboard (3m x 1.5m) and mount it on the front wall directly behind the teacher desk at eye level (~1m above floor).\n9. Add a ceiling-mounted projector: aligned on the centerline of the room at ~2.7m height, aimed at the whiteboard.\n10. Define and place a tall bookshelf (2m h x 1m w x 0.4m d) filled with book objects against the right side wall.\n11. Define and mount a circular wall clock (0.5m diameter) on the left side wall near the ceiling.\n12. Create a potted plant object (0.5m diameter pot, ~1m tall) and place it in the front-left corner near the entrance.\n13. Lay out multiple ceiling lights (e.g., 12 fixtures) in a 3x4 grid evenly spaced across the ceiling.\n14. Create wall poster objects (e.g., 4 educational charts, 1m x 0.7m each) and mount them on side and back walls.\n15. Define two waste bin objects (0.4m x 0.4m x 0.6m) and position one near the teacher’s desk and one at the back of the classroom.\n16. Add two large windows (2m w x 1.5m h) with curtains on the left wall, spaced evenly, at ~1.2m above floor.\n17. Apply materials: walls and floor in white or light neutral color; desks and chairs in specified wood tones; curtains in complementary light fabric.\n18. Verify all objects are placed at proper heights: desks and chairs on floor, mounted items on walls/ceiling.\n19. All seven fixes have been applied:

- **teacher_chair** now faces forward (rotation y = 180).  
- **whiteboard** is pulled out slightly (z = –4.925).  
- **bookshelf** shifted off the right wall (x = 7.25).  
- **wall_clock** nudged out of the left wall (x = –7.425).  
- **poster_1** & **poster_2** nudged off the left wall (x = –7.445).  
- **poster_3** nudged off the right wall (x = 7.445).  

All other objects remain unchanged.
